  <a name="subscription-share"></a><h2>Can a Gold subscription be shared?</h2>
  <p>Yes! We do not limit the number of computers that can access MindMup using a
  single subscription, because Gold is charged by the total storage capacity, not the
  number of users. Some examples when you might want to share the subscription
  are:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>enable the whole classroom store private maps securely and easily access them</li>
    <li>enable a group of people to discover each other's maps. </li>
  </ul>
  <p>
  All browser profiles authorised with the same subscription have full access to the
  documents saved under that subscription. Please keep your subscription secure and share
  only with people or computers you want to allow access to your files. If you
  are using a public computer (eg in a school or an internet cafe), please
  remember to de-authorise that browser profile after you are finished working,
  otherwise the next person using that computer might have access to your files.
  The two sections below explain how to authorise and deauthorise a browser
  profile.
  </p>
  <p>
  Please note that all the browser profiles with the same subscription use the same
  storage capacity, and each Gigabyte of storage costs 25 USD per year (so don't
  share your subscription with the world).</p>
</div>
