<a name="multiple-google"></a><h2>How to use a different Google account?</h2>
<p>If you are logged on to several Google accounts in the same browser profile, Google log-in will generally choose the first account only. Due to a limitation with the external Google interfaces
for authentication, there is not much we can do about account selection. For people who have multiple accounts, there are three good workarounds to ensure the right account is selected:</p>
<ul>
  <li>If using Chrome, use the <a href="https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/2364824?hl=en-GB">built-in browser support for multiple Google accounts</a>. This way, you can create separate
  browser profiles with only one account signed in</li>
  <li>Use your browser temporarily in private or incognito mode, logging in only one account to Google</li>
  <li>Log in using e-mail, where you will be able to enter the e-mail address associated with the correct Google account</li>
</ul>
