  <a name="secure"></a><h2>How secure is Gold Storage?</h2>
  <p>
  Gold Maps are physically stored on Amazon's S3 cloud and transported directly
  from your browser to Amazon using HTTPS. We rely on Amazon to provide
  resilience and backups, and we do not provide any additional backups or
  security over Amazon's mechanisms. For more information on Amazon S3 storage <a
    href="http://aws.amazon.com/s3/" target="_blank">see their product page</a>.
  </p>
</div>
<div class="row">
  <a name="managing-files"></a><h2>How to manage maps stored on Gold storage?</h2>
  <p>
  To see maps stored on your Gold storage, just click <strong>View&gt;Mindmup&nbsp;Gold&nbsp;Maps</strong>. You can click any map name in the list
  to open and view it.
  </p>
  <p>To delete a map from your Gold storage, click on the trash icon (<i class="fa fa-trash"></i>) next to the map name.</p>
  <p>Maps automatically get named based on the text in the central node the first time you save them. You can change the central node
  text later, but maps will not be renamed in order to keep the same URL. To rename a map, you should first export it to your local 
  disk (<strong>File&gt;Export&nbsp;To&nbsp;Local&nbsp;Disk&gt;MindMup</strong>), delete the original map as described above, 
  then import a map from the local disk (<strong>File&gt;Open/Import&nbsp;From&nbsp;Local&nbsp;Disk&gt;MindMup</strong>), then
  save to MindMup Gold. This will save the map using the new name.</p>
  <p>To change a map from private to public, or the other way around, just select <strong>File&gt;Save&nbsp;as</strong> and choose the
  appropriate option from the menu. </p>
